<title>UK: INSTANT VIEW - British inflation target.</title>
<headline>INSTANT VIEW - British inflation target.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Following is a selection of analysts' views on British Chancellor of the Exchequer Gordon Brown's announcement on Thursday that he was setting a 2.5 percent inflation target, with deviations of one percentage point requiring an open letter of explanation from the Bank of England governor.</p>
<p>SIMON BRISCOE, NIKKO EUROPE</p>
<p>&quot;The apparently strict monetary policy regime that was unveiled a month ago is now being diluted. The key point is that the inflation 'cap' has been replaced by a spot target.&quot;</p>
